The fairways feature two key innovations known as Facewrap Technology and Spinsistency to deliver more distance and spin predictability. Just as it sounds, Facewrap refers to the G425's face design that extends up and into the crown, as well as into the sole. This unique design works in harmony with the thin, high-strength steel maraging face to provide increased flexing, resulting in greater distance and high launching shots. The most common miss-hit for fairway woods is low on the face, which dramatically increases spin and kills distance potential. In order to combat this problem, PING developed Spinsistency. Spinsistency consists of a complex face curvature that modifies the roll profile, mainly low on the face, where the loft decreases approximately 2.5 to normalize spin and increase ball speed. During PING's testing, human and robots alike displayed greatly improved distance, specifically on shots struck low on the face. Description: Ever since hook production started in the 1870s, Mustad has manufactured an impressive number of different fish hook patterns for a vast array of fishing methods. Such a long history and experience has given us invaluable knowledge about what it takes to perfect a fish hook for a specific type of fishing as well as all round freshwater and saltwater fishing. Mustad has manufactured hooks since 1877, but now the company has made an effort to be able to offer all the tackle you need when you go fishing. MUSTAD hooks are made from premium hi-carbon steel, which gives the hooks maximum strength. MUSTAD?s unique tempering process ensures even strength and high quality. Before being tempered the hooks are forged, which in this context means that the hook wire is a bit compressed. By doing this, the strength of the hook is increased by over 30%! The Mustad 94840 fly hook is the standard for dry fly fishing hooks. You will find the 94840 in a multitude of fly patterns. Turned down eye, bronzed finish.

The new Srixon ZX4 Irons are a fully hollow iron set that boast powerful forgiveness, while maintaining the brand's signature look and forged feel. For the first time ever, golfers seeking game improvement performance can experience Srixon's legendary irons. When designing the ZX4 Irons, Srixon utilized artificial intelligence and machine learning to create, test and improve face designs. After thousands of iterations, Srixon's automated intelligent design software produced MainFrame. This unique architecture consists of milling a variable thickness pattern (made up of grooves, channels and cavities) into the back of the iron's face. After two years of refinement, Srixon settled on a final face design that offers greatly improved COR by maximizing flex at impact. Description: A fresh take on the classic soft plastic jerkbait, the Googan Baits Dart is a versatile twitchbait capable of enticing bites from bass of all sizes. Molded with a slender baitfish profile, the Dart's slim body and forked tail allow for a highly reactive response to twitches of the rod tip. The Dart will respond with erratic changes in direction followed by a graceful glide when worked. The sharp contrast between the twitch and glide actions is what triggers the irresistible response from bass to strike. Extremely versatile in its approach, the Dart can be rigged on a jig head, weighted swimbait hook, unweighted Texas rig, as a swim jig trailer, and more. The slim profile makes it great for coming through grass when rigged weedless, but is equally as deadly around suspended bass.

This all-new shape creates more area to put extra mass, allowing Tour Edge to precisely position weight in the head to produce an ultra-low and deep center of gravity. The result is an extremely high MOI rating surpassing 5000 grams per cubic CM, making the E522 extremely stable and forgiving. Simply put, Houdini Sole makes this the highest launching and easiest to hit driver Tour Edge has ever produced. The second piece of technology found in the E522 is known as Diamond Face 2.0, a major breakthrough in face technology. Diamond Face consists of 42 "mini-trampolines" behind the face which flex and rebound to rocket the ball of the club head for explosive ball speed and distance. As an added benefit, Diamond Face improves performance on off-center hits and reduces spin. If you, like many golfers, find yourself fighting the dreaded slice, the E522 has you covered. The driver's offset design and strategically placed heel draw-bias weighting are sure to help you avoid the right side of the golf course, with the added benefit of increasing launch angle. Tour Edge fits the E522 with the extremely lightweight Mitsubishi FUBUKI HL graphite shaft to help maximize velocity and fight the fade. Name: Cobra Men's Ltd X Iron Steel 8 Piece | Right | Size 4-PW
Description: html-body [data-pb-style=JIH1W4U]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}When it came time to develop the new LTDx Irons, Cobra started at the core, infusing the club's with PWR-COR and PWRSHELL Technologies. The result, is an iron possessing a staggering combination of ball speed, distance, and forgiveness. PWR-COR Technology consists of a multi-layer weighting system featuring a steel bar suspended within a polymer injected casing. The design promotes maximum flex of the body, face and sole at impact, creating an elastic rebound effect that delivers explosive ball speeds. With its forged cup face and deep undercut cavity, PWRSHELL Technology works harmoniously with PWR-COR, allowing the face to flex even further. As a consequence, more energy is returned to the ball for enhanced total distance. Using hit pattern data, Cobra modeled the variable thickness face to preserve ball speed in common mishit locations, ensuring that poorly struck shots travel nearly the same distance as center strikes. Stock shaft offerings include two offerings from KBS. The steel Tour 90 is designed for players seeking higher trajectory, additional spin and maximum distance. The graphite PGI weighs significantly less, which helps elevate club head speed, yet still maintains the same ball flight characteristics, tight tolerances, dispersion and control as its steel sibling. Cobra LTDx Irons Feature: Designed for peak ball speed and distance Multi-layer PWR-COR weighting system promotes maximum flex of the body, face and sole at impact for powerful ball speed PWRSHELL Forged Face Cup design increases ball speed across a wider area on the face Speed Tuned Weighting with an 8g toe weight for enhanced stability Stock Steel Shaft: KBS Tour 90 (Regular 95g, Stiff 102g) Stock Graphite Shaft: KBS PGI (Lite/Senior 60g, Regular 70g, Stiff 80g) Stock Grip: Lamkin Crosslin

Description: Designed with a strikingly realistic profile and lifelike appendages, the Savage Gear 3D Lizard is about as close as you can get to the real thing. Molded with a bulbous head, four realistic leg appendages, and an oversized swimming tail, the 3D Lizard blends anatomical accuracy with a pulsating swimming action to fool even the most discerning of bass. These baits are molded from a supple yet highly durable soft plastic formula that can withstand repeated strikes from aggressive bass. Scent infusion helps trigger feeding responses from bass that may be wary or experience heavy fishing pressure. The 3D Lizard can be fished with a variety of methods, including Texas rigs, Carolina Rigs, or even as a flipping bait. Anglers will find these lures to be effective year round, but truly shine when fished shallow during the spawn when bass are aggressively protecting their nests from invaders such as salamanders.

Cobra elected to leave the Baffler Rails off of the 3-wood in order to account for a sweeping, shallow swing path. The LTDx MAX features the distance and speed performance of the standard LTDx model with heel-weighting that provides a draw-bias and enhanced slice correction. Name: Tour Edge Exotics C722 Hybrids in Blue | Right
Description: html-body [data-pb-style=JC5NH88]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}The ultra-compact, player's Tour Edge Exotics C722 Hybrids feature revolutionary high-flying, low-spinning RyzerSole Technology while bringing the ultimate in power and forgiveness through Tour Edge's groundbreaking Diamond VFT technology. The aforementioned RyzerSole Technology includes a sole rail and added weight that extends from the leading edge to the trailing edge of the club. As a result the E722 is endowed with a super-low, forward CG that produces high-launching shots with amazingly low spin rates, decreased turf interaction and maximum ball speed of the face. In order to truly maximize ball speed, Tour Edge equips the C722 with Diamond Face VFT Technology. Diamond Face is a unique construction consisting of 41 diamond shapes of variable thickness behind the face. The shapes act as "mini-trampolines", rocketing the ball of the club head at explosive speeds, as well as expanding the sweet spot to the outer reaches of the face. Determined by robotic testing, and validated by player testing, every shaft in the Exotics 722 Series has been SpeedTested to find the optimal shaft pairing for every flex. Stock shaft offerings include KBS' TGI, Fujikura's Ventus Blue, and Mitsubishi's TENSEI AV RAW White graphite shafts. Tour Edge Exotics C722 Hybrids Feature: Player preferred, compact iron-like design with a square-toe face that provides the ultimate versatility Low CG RyzerSole sole rail technology produces high-launching, low spin bombs 10-Gram adjustable weight located directly behind the face creates super-low CG that produces lower spin Maraging steel face with Diamond Face CFT technology creates full face forgiveness and amazing ball speed Adjustable hosel allows loft to be adjusted +/- 1.5 degrees up or down Stock Shafts: KBS TGI  Fujikura Ventus Blue

Name: PING G410 Plus Driver in Black | Left
Description: html-body [data-pb-style=FP6VSIO]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll;border-style:none;border-width:1px;border-radius:0;margin:0 0 10px;padding:10px}html-body [data-pb-style=OMLN1D4]{border-style:none;border-width:1px;border-radius:0;margin:0;padding:0}The Ping G410 Plus Driver represents a turning point in Ping's history; Ping started with the ground breaking G400 Max, made it hotter, faster and then added an adjustable weight. Golfers can now experience Ping's remarkable driver technology and dial in their ideal ball flight. The G410 Plus Driver is more than just a G400 Max with an adjustable weight. The 410's new creased crown and Dragonfly Technology combine to create a stiff, ultra-thin, weight-saving crown. Ping repositioned the weight to optimize the center of gravity location and increase forgiveness. Ping's unique forging and patented heat-treatment process make the G410's precision machined T9S+ face thinner and hotter in the impact area to elevate ball speed across the entire face. The forged face and internal geometry of the head are instrumental in producing the powerful feel feel and sound of the G410. Ping's new, patented lightweight and aerodynamic hosel expands from five to eight settings, offering loft (0, +1, +1.5, -1, -1.5) and lie adjustments (including up to 3 flatter than standard) to optimize ball flight. In Ping's continuing effort to optimize the entire club, Ping's team developed the next generation of Alta CB (counter balanced) shaft as the stock option in the G410 Driver. The lightweight, higher-launching Alta CB Red 55 is engineered with an eight-gram counterweight in the grip end of the shaft, shifting the CG higher and allowing for more head weight, which increases energy transfer, momentum, ball speed and forgiveness. Name: Tour Edge Hot Launch E522 Driver 16010580- Senior Right-Handed
Description: Tour Edge Hot Launch E522 Driver The Extreme Game Improvement Hot Launch E522 Driver is all about ease of use. The 460cc driver made from premium 6-4 Titanium features extreme Moment of Inertia properties with a major emphasis on ease of launch, playability and correcting miss-hits and slices to go straighter. Features:  Houdini Sole Technology - The Houdini Sole design innovation pushes weight back as much as possible in a driver design. This design created extra mass to precisely position weight in the head for an ultra-low and deep Center of Gravity, optimizing launch conditions and greatly improving forgiveness off the face. High Moment of Inertia - An extremely high MOI rating surpassing 5000 grams per cubic cm2, makes the E522 Driver an extremely stable and powerful driver. This increased MOI will improve ball speed on miss-hits and will keep shots straighter, while the back and low CG positioning creates high-flying, powerful tee shots. Diamond Face 2.0 / Cup Face Technology - The Hot Launch E522 Driver features Diamond Face 2.0 technology with 42 different thick and thin diamond shapes behind the face of the metals for an enhanced sweet spot. Different variables of thick and thin diamond shapes or  mini-trampolines  behind the face combine with a Cup Face construction to produce greater face flex, faster ball speeds and better performance on off-center hits. Heel Weighted/Slice Fighting Offset/Shallow Face Designs - Offset designs are combined with a heel sole weight to provide the ultimate in slice fighting technology. The strategically placed heel draw-bias weight allows the face to square up at impact for straighter ball flight that helps golfers avoid the right side of the course. A super-shallow face design produces higher launch angles and extreme ease of launch. Control Length Shafts - A Control Length Shaft system means optimized, shorter shaft lengths that were designed specifically for the E522 Driver to greatly improve accuracy, control and to offer maxed out Smash Factor ratings for the club head. The Control Length Shaft leads to more players hitting the center of the clubface. Premium Mitsubishi Fubuki HL Shaft - The E522 Driver comes stock with super-light FUBUKI HL graphite shafts by Mitsubishi Chemical that range from 45-grams to 55-grams depending on the flex. Stock Shaft - Mitsubishi Fubuki HL (50-gram A-Flex, 50-gram Regular Flex, 55-gram Stiff Flex). Grip - Lamkin Z5 Rubber available in Undersize, Standard and Midsize. Name: Hyperlite Eden Wakeboard
Description: Creating a women’s shape to take their skills to the next level was the goal behind the new Eden 2.0. Learning from other asymmetrical designs, we found that creating a shorter but more effective edge on a rider’s toe-side made hard to learn wake jumps that much easier. This is because there is less rail to initiate when applying toe-side pressure. Once set, the smoother toe-side transition is then held by the Eden 2.0’s thinner profile molded-in fin, creating less drag and a better release off the top of the wake. Subtle Toe-Side Footbed Risers were also added to help a rider create more leverage when pressure is applied. The longer, more traditional heel-side edge compliments this asymmetrical design by allowing the natural body position of a rider to generate stability and speed into the wake without a loss of pop due to reduced surface area. The Eden 2.0 has been tested and proven to be the best choice for a rider looking to master the foundations of wakeboarding. Description: Modeled from a 3D Scan of an actual shiner, the Savage Gear Pulse Tail Shiner LT Swimbaits offer an incredibly lifelike action and a rigging system that helps you land more fish. These swimbaits feature Savage Gear's patent pending Pulse Tail design that creates a subtle, incredibly realistic tail kick at a variety of speeds. The Pulse Tail Shiner LT (Line-Thru) Swimbaits utilize a line-through rigging system that allows the bait to detach from the hook when fighting the fish. This denies the fish the ability to use the large swimbait as leverage to throw the hook, ultimately resulting in fewer lost fish. These swimbaits are perfect for use when covering large areas of open water, over the tops of grass and weed beds, or slow rolled along deep bottoms. Offered in a variety of color patterns inspired by common forage fish species, there's bound to be the perfect color to match the hatch when targeting the biggest fish in your local waters.

Description: html-body [data-pb-style=Q79LTAG]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}By replacing heavy steel with a lightweight core in the all-new Cleveland RTX ZipCore Wedges, Cleveland was able to shift the center of gravity, which raises MOI, adds spin, enhances control and boosts consistency on all your shots. New UltiZip Grooves help maximize the ZipCore's performance and consistency. The grooves are sharper to cut through grass more efficiently. They're deeper, which helps channel debris for better contact. Finally, the grooves are more tightly packed, leading to increased edge contact and greater consistency. Three grinds are available in the RTX ZipCore: The Mid Sole has a v-shaped sole with trailing edge relief. This grind is perfect for all-around wedge play, players with a neutral to steep attack angle, and medium or soft conditions. The Low Sole is a c-shaped grind featuring relief on the heel, toe and trailing edge for superior versatility. The Low Sole is perfect for finesse and open faced shops, a neutral to shallow attack angle, and medium or firm conditions. The Full Sole is a classic, stable design, with extra bounce as you open the face. This grind is perfect for bunker and rough shots, a neutral to steep attack angle, and medium or soft conditions. Cleveland elected to use both the True Temper Dynamic Gold Spinner Tour Issue and KBS Tour-V shafts in the ZipCore, and for good reason. The Spinner provides all the characteristics of a tour issue wedge shaft, but is built to help generate extra spin and tour-level stopping power. True Temper designed the Spinner to have a similar profile to the Dynamic Gold S200, but tuned it for wedge play. The tested and tour-proven KBS Tour-V produces a lower-mid trajectory, mid ball spin and an incredibly tight shot dispersion. Cleveland RTX ZipCore Wedges - Black Satin Feature: Low-density Zip

The high, forward CG position boosts MOI, improves distance control, trajectory control, feel and stability. To provide you with maximum spin, every SM8's grooves are 100% inspected Spin Milled Grooves. The wedges receive a proprietary heat treatment that doubles groove durability. Six tour-proven sole grinds provide a precision fit. If you weren't already sold, know that Bob Vokey's wedges have been the 1 wedge on tour since 2004, and the SM8's have already become the most played wedge model on the PGA Tour this year. Ideal for player with a shallower, more sweeping swing type. S Grind: Full sole narrowed by a trailing edge. Best for neutral to firm conditions and for players that control loft with their hands ahead of the ball. When it came time to design the new Srixon ZX Fairway Woods, Srixon obsessed over one thing: speed. This obsession led to a new breakthrough design called Rebound Frame. Whereas traditional fairway woods use a flexible face that compresses and decompresses at impact to propel the ball forward, Rebound Frame adds a second layer of flexibility. Together, the face and frame work like dual springs, transferring even more energy from the club head to the golf ball. By refocusing energy that's ordinarily lost, Rebound Frame is faster on every strike, especially center-face impacts. In fact, Srixon claims that even the most flexible fairway wood face simply cannot transfer as much energy as Rebound Frame's dual Flex Zones. On top of the fairway, you'll find a larger carbon crown than previous generations. Increasing the amount of strong, lightweight carbon fiber allowed Srixon to reposition mass low, deep, and around the perimeter, pushing MOI up and increasing forgiveness on every shot. Name: Raidlight Responsiv Ultra Trail Running Shoes
Description: Comfort is a key word when it comes to Ultra footwear. We developed a wide rounded forefoot allowing the foot to work unrestricted. An external heel cradle to support your foot as the fatigue sets in. Highly breathable, quick drying and durable fabrics keep the foot protected and an anatomically shaped tongue and cut away heel reduce pressure on nerves and tendons. All in this has the comfort of a slipper but the performance of a race car.  Underfoot the comfort word still reigns. The midsole is a full injection moulded system, giving long term durability and performance with exceptional rebound quality. Perfect for long days or multi-day trail. Shape is also important and the rolling sole profile allows a natural transition from heel, midfoot or forefoot strike. To keep the weight as low as possible we removed rubber from where it is not needed, you still get 4mm tread depth over the key grip areas, but the sole unit is 50% lighter than a normal sole.  Allowing you to balance lacing pressure over the top of the foot we developed the M-Lock band, this will allow you to have laces under less tension but still maintain foot hold on non technical terrain. Description: html-body [data-pb-style=Y3UV5HD]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}The PUMA PROADAPT ALPHACAT Disc Golf Shoes feature all-new, proprietary ADAPT Foam cushioning. Utilizing a mixture of the highest-grade EVA cushioning and impact-resistant foam that provides excellent dimensional stability, ADAPT Foam delivers ultimate comfort and high energy return. The ALPHACAT's outsole is comprised of two different, unique areas. Around the perimeter, a high-durometer, abrasion-resistant TPU chassis offers stability, while multiple shapes of lugs provide incredible ground-gripping traction. On the interior, anatomically shaped Crystal Rubber follows your gait, delivering an easy ride, extra grip and eliminating slippage on the course. Description: Specially designed for the increasingly popular technique of Neko Rigging, the Missile Baits Quiver Worm will help you take your finesse bass fishing game to new heights. Featuring the signature ribbed body that fans of Missile Baits will immediately recognize, the Quiver Worm will displace water and exude a subtle body shimmy as it skitters its way head-first across the bottom. The worm's wide, blunted head is perfectly configured to hold nail weights of multiple sizes securely, while the flattened spade-tail effectively catches water as the bait moves and provides an attractive flicker that bass can't help but lend their attention to. Anglers will also find success with these finesse baits when fished on a Texas-rig or Tokyo-rig. Available in two sizes and a variety of Missile's popular color patterns, the Quiver Worm is the perfect bait for both novice and expert Neko Rig anglers.

Stock shaft offerings include Fujikura's Air Speeder, Fujikura's Ventus Red, Fujikura's Ventus Blue, and Mitsubishi's TENSEI AV RAW Blue graphite shafts. To achieve this new level of MOI and performance, PING engineers combined key technologies from the G400 Max and G410 Plus, resulting in a 26-gram tungsten moveable weight in the rear of the driver. Without PING's weight saving Dragon Fly Crown technology, this would not have been possible. The weight can be positioned over a smaller area than G410 models, thus shifting the center of gravity lower and farther back, without sacrificing performance. In fact, the G425 Max produces an average MOI increase of 14% compared to the G410 Plus, regardless of whether the weight is secured in the neutral, draw or fade setting. While talk is great, the numbers back PING's claims about the G425 Max up, with three combinations of weight position and loft measuring north of a whopping 10,000 MOI. Description: Panther Martin Inline Spinners are among the most iconic lures ever produced. The original inline spinner, Panther Martin's have become a staple in the trout fishing community over the past 60 years, and have been proven to be undeniably effective on anything from stocked rainbows and browns to giant native steelhead and salmon. Over the past few decades, Panther Martin Inline Spinners have also proven to be effective when targeting bass, walleye, panfish, pike, pickerel, muskie, and many other species. Panther Martin Spinners are the world's easiest and fastest spinning inline spinners thanks to their signature shaft-through blade design. This simplistic approach minimizes the use of unnecessary hardware on the lure, ensuring proper blade rotation time and time again without fail. The Convex/Concave spinning blade sends out a subtle vibration and flash that predatory fish will find irresistible. The heavy weighted bodies will aid in casting distance and running depth, allowing you to cover large amounts of water with this highly effective presentation. Each Panther Martin Inline Spinner features a razor sharp premium quality treble hook designed to keep fish pinned.

Name: Cobra Ltd X Max Driver in Black | Right
Description: html-body [data-pb-style=VNO5OYG]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}Thanks to years of advancements in materials, weight placement, aerodynamics and artificial intelligence, the new Cobra LTDx MAX Driver enters a new realm of speed and forgiveness. As a matter of fact, the LTDx MAX is Cobra's first driver to achieve zero CGna and over 5000 MOI, a true triumph in engineering. As was previously mentioned, Cobra utilized artificial intelligence when designing the LTDx. Specifically, AI played an integral role in crafting the driver's face. Known as H.O.T. Face Technology, the design consists of 15 HOT zones with strategic thicknesses to increase smash factor and ball speed across a much wider area of the face. The result is the hottest, most forgiving driver face in Cobra's history. Stability is an equally important component in terms of a driver's performance. In the golf industry, stability is measured using MOI, which refers the club head's tendency to rotate around the ball at impact. As MOI increases, the driver's face is more likely to stay pointed towards the target, even on mishits. In order to pull off the lofty 5000 plus MOI rating, Cobra's R & D team developed a multi-material chassis comprised of a lightweight carbon crown, lightweight sole plates, and a reinforced Titanium Speed Frame. The LTDx MAX is the most forgiving model in the LTDx family, and is highlighted by added heel weighting that provides a draw bias to help eliminate the dreaded slice. Stock shafts include Project X's mid-launching, low-spinning HZRDUS RDX Blue, Project X's mid-launching, mid-spinning HZRDUS Smoke iM10, and UST's high-launching, high-spinning Helium NanoCore. Description: A more snack sized version of the original, the Strike King KVD Baby Sexy Frog is the perfect topwater frog for downsizing your profile when fishing over heavy cover. Just like its predecessor, the KVD Baby Sexy Frog is 100% snag proof for fishing in pads and heavy vegetation. Its smaller body and more compact profile is perfect for when fish are keyed in on smaller forage, or when smaller pond fish are proving to be difficult to hook up to on a larger frog. These frogs are built around a heavy duty double pronged frog hook strategically nested against the hollow body to protect the hook points from snags. When the fish bites, the body compresses and exposes the hook points and its game on. The keeled belly of the frog makes for an easy back-and-forth walking action that triggers strikes from bass hiding in grass mats and along scum lines. The KVD Baby Sexy Frog is the hollow body frog to reach for when downsizing your profile means putting more fish in the boat.

This revolutionary design, known as 60X Carbon Twist Face, is comprised of sixty layers of carbon fiber which have been strategically engineered to optimize energy transfer and deliver explosive ball speeds. Not only is 60X Carbon Twist Face 44% lighter than an equivalent titanium face, it is also 11% larger than SIM2 and SIM2 Max drivers, and nearly 20% larger than the original SIM driver. As a result, the face is not only faster, but extremely forgiving, and capable of delivering tremendous speed across a larger area of the face. One might think that revolutionizing the driver face would suffice, but TaylorMade didn't stop there, encasing the 60X Carbon Twist Face in a polyurethane cover featuring ground breaking nanotexture technology. Nanotexture allowed engineers to fine tune launch and spin, optimizing total distance, regardless of playing conditions, or where the ball is struck on the face. Earlier, it was mentioned that the 60X Carbon Twist Face saves an extraordinary amount of weight compared to traditional titanium, and TaylorMade put the weight savings to great use, positioning weight low and deep in the head. In comparison to the Stealth Plus+, the Stealth boasts 15% more MOI, making it much more stable than its low-spin sibling. Two stock shaft offerings are available in the Stealth, including Fujikura's Ventus Red and Aldila's ASCENT Red, both of which are graphite. While both shafts are intended to increase launch conditions and carry distances, the Ventus Red is the higher-launching, higher-spinning option of the two. Name: Titleist Vokey SM8 Brushed Steel Wedge 15003504- Left-Handed D Grind
Description: Titleist Vokey SM8 Brushed Steel WedgeThe shift that will reshape your wedge game. SM8 features a center of gravity that is pushed forward from the face, through the use of high density tungsten, producing a more consistent, pure strike that helps you hit your target more often.SM8 takes the next innovative leap - pushing CG forward of the face in the high lofts. Maintaining the vertical, progressive center of gravity, while improving the CG depth (forward/back). This produces improved feel and stability, resulting in closer proximity to the hole.To achieve the CG heights that produce exceptional ball flight, and push the CG forward of the face in the high lofts, Voke's team lengthened the hosel and counter balanced this weight with a tungsten weight low in the toe. The result is high, forward center of gravity and increased MOI. For golfers, this means improved feel, improved ball flight, and a club face that simply wants to square at impact for more consistent results.Wedge Grinds:F Grind - is an all-purpose grind that is particularly suited for full shots and shots hit with a square face. Ideal for players who prefer a traditional wedge sole. The F grind is the most played sand wedge on Tour including Justin Thomas, Ian Poulter and Charlie Hoffman.M Grind - Voke s favorite, is designed for players that like to rotate the club face open and closed to manufacture shots around the green. Ideal for players with a shallower, more sweeping swing type who play shots from a variety of clubface positions. Played by Charles Howell III, Patrick Cantlay and Cam Smith.S Grind - features a full sole that has been narrowed by a trailing edge grind, giving it a faster feel through the turf. This grind is best for neutral to firm conditions and for players that like to control loft with their hands ahead or behind the ball. Played by Jordan Spieth, Adam Scott and Lanto Griffin.D Grind - blends versatility from a heel, toe, and trailing edge grind and forgiveness with its high measured bounce. The D Grind is ideal for players with a steeper angle of attack who play shots from a variety of clubface positions.L Grind - lowest bounce option in the mix. The heel, toe, and trailing edge relief allow for maximum greenside versatility. This club is perfect for firm conditions and designed for precise players. It is ideal for players that have complete control of impact looking for maximum shot-making versatility. Played by Jordan Spieth, Jimmy Walker, and JT Poston.K Grind - highest bounce wedge in the lineup, and is the ultimate bunker club. The K Grind is a wide, full sole wedge with enhanced camber to make it forgiving from a variety of sand and turf conditions. Played by Justin Thomas, Adam Scott and Webb Simpson.

While speed is a prerequisite for distance, launch and spin are equally important factors. By moving the center of gravity low and forward using up 27g of tungsten, Callaway's groundbreaking Tungsten Speed Cartridge reduces spin. Additionally, the new Speed Tuned A.I. Face optimizes launch and spin for each model and loft in the fairway lineup. The ST MAX D is the highest launching fairway wood in the Rogue lineup, and utilizes a slightly closed face, more upright lie angle and additional weight in the heel to promote a powerful draw. This model fits players that need the most shot shape correction and help fighting the slice. Callaway Rogue ST MAX D Fairway Woods Feature: High-launch with a powerful draw bias A.I. Description: The Gene Larew Biffle Bug is a deadly creature style bait perfect for a wide variety of techniques. Designed with multiple features from other top performing baits, the Biffle Bug combines a unique body construction with a variety of lifelike appendages to create a bait that excels in almost any situation. The head of the bait is solid to allow for a secure hook hold, while the rest of the body is hollow. This ovular shaped hollow body construction is designed to hold glass rattles or scented attractants. For a lifelike swimming action, the Biffle Bug features two swimming legs with special foot pads that produce a hyper active kicking motion while the bait is retrieved. The body is covered with ridges and has six micro-pulsating tentacles attached to the sides and a flexible convex tail that wags and sways while the bait swims. For a presentation that perfectly depicts a crawfish scurrying across the bottom, fish the Biffle Bug on a jointed football head like the Gene Larew Biffle HardHead Jig in a weight just heavy enough to keep in contact with the bottom on a steady retrieve. Allow the head to bang around on rocky bottoms and submerged structure, causing the jig to erratically jolt and change direction when deflecting off of obstacles. This technique has produced numerous tournament victories and is a great alternative to deepwater crankbait fishing. The Biffle Bug can also be fished in a variety of other ways including Texas rigged, Carolina rigged, on a stand-up head, or as a jig trailer.

Description: html-body [data-pb-style=JDHYXYT]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}After twenty years of development, the TaylorMade Stealth HD Driver unveils a new technology that buries the era of titanium faces. This revolutionary design, known as 60X Carbon Twist Face, is comprised of sixty layers of carbon fiber which have been strategically engineered to optimize energy transfer and deliver explosive ball speeds. Not only is 60X Carbon Twist Face 44% lighter than an equivalent titanium face, it is also 11% larger than SIM2 and SIM2 Max drivers, and nearly 20% larger than the original SIM driver. As a result, the face is not only faster, but extremely forgiving, and capable of delivering tremendous speed across a larger area of the face. One might think that revolutionizing the driver face would suffice, but TaylorMade didn't stop there, encasing the 60X Carbon Twist Face in a polyurethane cover featuring ground breaking nanotexture technology. Nanotexture allowed engineers to fine tune launch and spin, optimizing total distance, regardless of playing conditions, or where the ball is struck on the face. Often, draw biased drivers promote a right-to-left ball flight at the expensive of forgiveness, but not the Stealth HD. TaylorMade utilized the aforementioned weight saved from 60X Carbon Twist Face to shift the inertia generator closer to the heel. In doing so, the HD is able to maintain its draw-bias, while simultaneously possessing the highest MOI and stability in the Stealth family of drivers. TaylorMade outfits the Stealth HD with Fujikura's Air Speeder 45 graphite shaft. The Air Speeder's unique lightweight design enhances swing speed and ball speed to generate more carry distance and longer drives. TaylorMade Stealth HD Driver Features: 60X Carbon Twist Face is 44% lighter than equivalent titanium, while also being 11% larger than SIM2

As a matter of fact, the LTDx MAX is Cobra's first driver to achieve zero CGna and over 5000 MOI, a true triumph in engineering. As was previously mentioned, Cobra utilized artificial intelligence when designing the LTDx. Specifically, AI played an integral role in crafting the driver's face. Known as H.O.T. Face Technology, the design consists of 15 HOT zones with strategic thicknesses to increase smash factor and ball speed across a much wider area of the face. The result is the hottest, most forgiving driver face in Cobra's history. Stability is an equally important component in terms of a driver's performance. In the golf industry, stability is measured using MOI, which refers the club head's tendency to rotate around the ball at impact. As MOI increases, the driver's face is more likely to stay pointed towards the target, even on mishits. In order to pull off the lofty 5000 plus MOI rating, Cobra's R & D team developed a multi-material chassis comprised of a lightweight carbon crown, lightweight sole plates, and a reinforced Titanium Speed Frame. The LTDx MAX is the most forgiving model in the LTDx family, and is highlighted by added heel weighting that provides a draw bias to help eliminate the dreaded slice. Stock shafts include Project X's mid-launching, low-spinning HZRDUS RDX Blue, Project X's mid-launching, mid-spinning HZRDUS Smoke iM10, and UST's high-launching, high-spinning Helium NanoCore. As a result, the face is not only faster, but extremely forgiving, and capable of delivering tremendous speed across a larger area of the face. One might think that revolutionizing the driver face would suffice, but TaylorMade didn't stop there, encasing the 60X Carbon Twist Face in a polyurethane cover featuring ground breaking nanotexture technology. Nanotexture allowed engineers to fine tune launch and spin, optimizing total distance, regardless of playing conditions, or where the ball is struck on the face. Earlier, it was mentioned that the 60X Carbon Twist Face saves an extraordinary amount of weight compared to traditional titanium, and TaylorMade put the weight savings to great use, equipping the Stealth Plus+ with an adjustable sliding weight. Draw, fade, and neutral settings allow golfers dial in the perfect shot shape by shifting mass along the sole. TaylorMade outfits the Stealth Plus+ with Project X's HZRDUS Smoke Red RDX and Mitsubishi's Kai'li White graphite shafts. Name: TaylorMade M4 Driver in Red | Right | Size S | 10.5
Description: html-body [data-pb-style=OR4IGI6]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}The TaylorMade M4 Driver features a suite of ground breaking technology and revolutionary club designs, the most notable of which is called Twist Face. Twist Face is TaylorMade's new corrective face curvature, which helps mishits fly farther and straighter. Twist Face's toe is aimed farther right and lofted up in comparison the center of the face. Conversely, the heel aims farther left and has less loft than the center of the club face. The result of this new curvature is a face that actively combats the low-left ball flight on a toe strike and the high-right ball flight of a heel strike. Also new to the M4 is the Hammerhead slot. The outside of the slot is reinforced, allowing for a thinner, lighter, more flexible face. This results in a larger sweet spot. Additionally, the center of the Hammerhead slot helps generate higher ball speed and lower spin on shots struck lower on the face. The M4 is long and straight, but that's a claim every manufacturer makes. TaylorMade, and only TaylorMade, can say they make a driver that actively corrects mishits. TaylorMade M4 Driver Features: Twist Face curvature with a corrective face angle on off-center hits engineered to reduce side spin and deliver straighter shots Hammerhead Slot with reinforced outer portions allows for a lighter, more flexible face, resulting in a larger sweet spot Center portion of the Hammerhead Slot increases ball speed low on the face and reduces unwanted spin for added distance Geocoustic Sole is reduced in volume to create a larger, more forgiving face and a solid, explosive sound at impact Stock Shaft: Fujikura Atmos Red 5 Stock Grip: TM Dual Feel 360 (.620 Round 47g) Headcover included NO wrench included Authorized TaylorMade Retailer Buy TaylorMade M4 Drivers | TaylorMade M4 Driver in Red | Right

Name: Ronix Flyweight Bat Tail Wakesurfer
Description: We took our classic Thruster that’s known for high speed carves for days and throwing down the biggest bottom turns and modernized it in the blue room. The result is a new thinner profile, wider compact Bat Tail outline – designed for the updated, bigger, steeper boat wake. This new hard charger gets to point B quicker and has more smack off the wake for added hangtime. This year we varied the volume of the board by putting more emphasis on altering the width and less on the length. So now you can ride a big board with a very stable overall ride and a lot of drive on a small wake – but still have a short tip length that sits easier in the pocket of a boat wake. Each length varies slightly but the overall volume changes quite a bit because of the contrast in the width of the respective model. Short, medium, long – have now been replaced by narrow, medium, wide, and XL. Now big guys can enjoy shortboard performance with a 4';';7" XL, while others can enjoy a board that rolls over on edge with ease on our new 4';';4" Narrow. By removing the adjustable hosel and opting for a lightweight shaft, the XL Lite saves 12 grams in comparison to the standard Launcher XL. This ultra-lightweight design pairs with a longer shaft to increase club head speed and distance. Thanks to a key piece of technology called Rebound Frame, the new Cleveland Launcher XL Lite Driver is the fastest, longest driver Cleveland has ever produced. Whereas traditional drivers use a flexible face that compresses and decompresses at impact to propel the ball forward, Rebound Frame adds a second layer of flexibility. Together, the face and frame work like dual springs, transferring even more energy from the club head to the golf ball. By refocusing energy that's ordinarily lost, Rebound Frame is faster on every strike, especially center-face impacts. In fact, Cleveland claims that even the most flexible driver face simply cannot transfer as much energy as Rebound Frame's dual Flex Zones. In terms of golf, MOI refers to an object's resistance to rotation, which is important, because when a club head strikes the ball off-center, it naturally wants to rotate. Rotation means the club is no longer facing its target, and errant shots will inevitably follow. In order to help combat misses and increase forgiveness, Cleveland added size to the Launcher XL. Description: html-body [data-pb-style=Q79LTAG]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}By replacing heavy steel with a lightweight core in the all-new Cleveland RTX ZipCore Wedges, Cleveland was able to shift the center of gravity, which raises MOI, adds spin, enhances control and boosts consistency on all your shots. New UltiZip Grooves help maximize the ZipCore's performance and consistency. The grooves are sharper to cut through grass more efficiently. They're deeper, which helps channel debris for better contact. Finally, the grooves are more tightly packed, leading to increased edge contact and greater consistency. Three grinds are available in the RTX ZipCore: The Mid Sole has a v-shaped sole with trailing edge relief. This grind is perfect for all-around wedge play, players with a neutral to steep attack angle, and medium or soft conditions. The Low Sole is a c-shaped grind featuring relief on the heel, toe and trailing edge for superior versatility. The Low Sole is perfect for finesse and open faced shops, a neutral to shallow attack angle, and medium or firm conditions. The Full Sole is a classic, stable design, with extra bounce as you open the face. This grind is perfect for bunker and rough shots, a neutral to steep attack angle, and medium or soft conditions. Cleveland elected to use both the True Temper Dynamic Gold Spinner Tour Issue and KBS Tour-V shafts in the ZipCore, and for good reason. The Spinner provides all the characteristics of a tour issue wedge shaft, but is built to help generate extra spin and tour-level stopping power. True Temper designed the Spinner to have a similar profile to the Dynamic Gold S200, but tuned it for wedge play. The tested and tour-proven KBS Tour-V produces a lower-mid trajectory, mid ball spin and an incredibly tight shot dispersion. Cleveland RTX ZipCore Wedges - Black Satin Feature: Low-density Zip

Description: html-body [data-pb-style=LCE6VGU]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll;border-style:none;border-width:1px;border-radius:0;margin:0 0 10px;padding:10px}html-body [data-pb-style=W057CSF]{border-style:none;border-width:1px;border-radius:0;margin:0;padding:0}html-body [data-pb-style=DVL8TKA]{text-align:center;margin:0;padding:0;border-style:none}html-body [data-pb-style=N377K4R],html-body [data-pb-style=TDWNTXF]{border-style:none;border-width:1px;border-radius:0;max-width:100%;height:auto}html-body [data-pb-style=RHGWI0C]{border-style:none;border-width:1px;border-radius:0;margin:0;padding:0}@media only screen and (max-width: 768px) { html-body [data-pb-style=DVL8TKA]{border-style:none} }PING G425 Fairway Woods are available in three models to fit all golfers and their desired ball flight: MAX (high MOI), LST (low spin), and SFT (draw bias). The fairways feature two key innovations known as Facewrap Technology and Spinsistency to deliver more distance and spin predictability. Just as it sounds, Facewrap refers to the G425's face design that extends up and into the crown, as well as into the sole. This unique design works in harmony with the thin, high-strength steel maraging face to provide increased flexing, resulting in greater distance and high launching shots. The most common miss-hit for fairway woods is low on the face, which dramatically increases spin and kills distance potential. In order to combat this problem, PING developed Spinsistency. Spinsistency consists of a complex face curvature that modifies the roll profile, mainly low on the face, where the loft decreases approximately 2.5 to normalize spin and increase ball speed. During PING's testing, human and robots alike displayed greatly improved distance, specifically on shots struck low on the face. Description: The SpoolTek Fatty Curly has a short, thick, baitfish profile designed to emulate pilchards, croakers, pinfish, finger mullet, herring, threadfin shad, gizzard shad, bunker and others. It features a curly swim tail for increased and versatile action. The lure's most unique feature is the internal spool containing a stainless steel leader that will separate from the lure when a fish strikes. This allows anglers to use lighter leaders attached to the eyelet of the lure, thus enhancing the action while preventing breakoffs due to the internal leader. It is also important to note that the hooked up fish will be unable to use the weight of the lure for leverage to throw the hook.

Name: Ronix Parks Wakeboard
Description: The oversize sweet spot of wakeboards. Parks has been wakeboarding for decades and through that time words like aggressive, reactive, and explosive have been replaced with smoother, faster, and predictable. That started with the rockerline – we created an arc that allows any rider to go into the wake blindfolded and they will know exactly how the board will lift off the water every time. This smooth take off also has more glide speed putting less strain on your body. Then we created a sidecut that allowed for more effective edge (grip) in the water when on rail – but when riding flat has you feeling more stable from the added surface area. Typically boards either have more sidecut or more surface area but rarely both. To give the rider fast, free cutbacks, we “borrowed” technology from the golf industry and ran dimples through the entire bottom of the board to reduce friction from the water and create a board that will break free unlike any shape out there.riding style rocker. Description: Designed and tested by legendary professional bass angler Body Duckett, the Duckett Fishing BD Shad Swimbaits are versatile big bass producers that will get the job done in just about any fishery. These segmented hard swimbaits feature a durable 3-joint design with a body profile that effectively mimics a variety of shad and baitfish species. The multi-jointed design allows for a lifelike "S" pattern swimming action that bass simply can't ignore. Fish the bait on a straight retrieve and use occasional twitches of the rod tip to make the bait erratically dart to the side to trigger strikes from curious followers. The BD Shad is equipped with lifelike 3D eyes and a natural hair tail fin for the ultimate lifelike appeal. With three different size options to choose from, the BD Shad is a great choice in swimbait whether you're looking to fill the livewell or hunting for that elusive giant that tops your personal best. All sizes feature tournament quality Kitana Hooks and split rings, allowing anglers to fish these swimbaits right out of the box with confidence.

Description: A versatile, long casting lure perfect for use both inshore and offshore, the Daiwa Zakana Jigs feature a rugged and thoughtful design that will bring you success in any waters. The Zakana Jig's long, streamlined profile is designed to effectively cut through both the air and water to provide extremely long casts even into the wind, and a subtle side-to-side swimming action with high speed retrieves. Once in motion, these jigs have the uncanny ability to remain horizontal and consistent in their swimming action thanks to the horizontal line tie, which is not often seen on these types of jigs. With a rugged through-wire construction and a heavy-duty VMC 9620 saltwater grade treble hook, the Zakana Jig is ready to go up against some of the toughest, hardest fighting game fish out there.

Description: Freshly redesigned for 2021 to meet the demands of tournament level bass anglers, the Shimano Curado Casting Rods showcase improved strength and casting performance over their predecessors. Now built on blanks featuring Shimano's famed Hi-Power X technology, the Curado Bass Rods are stronger and better performing than ever before. Hi-Power X blanks feature an outer layer of carbon tape that tightly winds the blank in opposite directions for enhanced torsional rigidity and heightened responsiveness. Hi-Power X blanks are revered for their ability to provide much more accurate casts by reducing blank twist and ovalization, while providing precise power transfer and control when fighting a fish. In terms of componentry, these rods are fitted with Fuji tangle-free K guides with FazLite inserts for precision line management and smooth casting. Shimano's CI4+ Reel Seats enhance sensitivity by more effectively transmitting vibrations into the hand and help contribute to the rod's lightweight and exceptionally well balanced feel. Durable EVA split grip handles provide a secure grip and comfort for all day casting. If a set of fairly priced tournament caliber bass rods is what you're looking for, you owe it to yourself to check out the newly redesigned Curado bass rods from Shimano.

Description: One of the most lifelike lures you'll ever see, Mustad InkVader Octopus Jig looks, moves, and even squirts black ink just like the real thing. Constructed from a highly supple yet super tough TPE material, the InkVader's eight tentacles respond to every movement of the rod tip with intense realism. The InkVader is most effectively deployed with a vertical jigging technique around reefs and other bottom structure where octopus may hide, but is also effective when slow trolled or even dead-sticked, as the slightest current or movement of the boat is enough to bring the free flowing tentacles to life. The heads are equipped with two different line-tie points to cater towards different approaches. Each InkVader Jig comes with 10 ink tablets that can be added to the head cavity, and will allow the lure to disperse a non-toxic and soluble black ink infused with actual octopus scent. This feature brilliantly mimics the behavior of an octopus fleeing from predators, and only heightens the InkVader's unprecedented realism. There are many different iterations of the InkVader to choose from, including three different sizes, ten different weight options, and nine photorealistic color patterns modeled after actual species of octopus.

New UltiZip Grooves help maximize the ZipCore's performance and consistency. The grooves are sharper to cut through grass more efficiently. They're deeper, which helps channel debris for better contact. Finally, the grooves are more tightly packed, leading to increased edge contact and greater consistency. Three grinds are available in the RTX ZipCore: The Mid Sole has a v-shaped sole with trailing edge relief. This grind is perfect for all-around wedge play, players with a neutral to steep attack angle, and medium or soft conditions. The Low Sole is a c-shaped grind featuring relief on the heel, toe and trailing edge for superior versatility. The Low Sole is perfect for finesse and open faced shops, a neutral to shallow attack angle, and medium or firm conditions. The Full Sole is a classic, stable design, with extra bounce as you open the face. This grind is perfect for bunker and rough shots, a neutral to steep attack angle, and medium or soft conditions. Cleveland elected to use both the True Temper Dynamic Gold Spinner Tour Issue and KBS Tour-V shafts in the ZipCore, and for good reason. The Spinner provides all the characteristics of a tour issue wedge shaft, but is built to help generate extra spin and tour-level stopping power. True Temper designed the Spinner to have a similar profile to the Dynamic Gold S200, but tuned it for wedge play. The tested and tour-proven KBS Tour-V produces a lower-mid trajectory, mid ball spin and an incredibly tight shot dispersion. Cleveland RTX ZipCore Wedges - Tour Satin Feature: Low-density ZipC

Name: Cobra Ltd X Driver in Black | Right
Description: html-body [data-pb-style=Y04KA9O]{justify-content:flex-start;display:flex;flex-direction:column;background-position:left top;background-size:cover;background-repeat:no-repeat;background-attachment:scroll}Thanks to years of advancements in materials, weight placement, aerodynamics and artificial intelligence, the new Cobra LTDx Drivers enter a new realm of speed and forgiveness. As a matter of fact, the LTDx is Cobra's first driver to achieve zero CGna and over 5000 MOI, a true triumph in engineering. As was previously mentioned, Cobra utilized artificial intelligence when designing the LTDx. Specifically, AI played an integral role in crafting the driver's face. Known as H.O.T. Face Technology, the design consists of 15 HOT zones with strategic thicknesses to increase smash factor and ball speed across a much wider area of the face. The result is the hottest, most forgiving driver face in Cobra's history. Stability is an equally important component in terms of a driver's performance. In the golf industry, stability is measured using MOI, which refers the club head's tendency to rotate around the ball at impact. As MOI increases, the driver's face is more likely to stay pointed towards the target, even on mishits. In order to pull off the lofty 5000 plus MOI rating, Cobra's R & D team developed a multi-material chassis comprised of a lightweight carbon crown, lightweight sole plates, and a reinforced Titanium Speed Frame. In terms of forgiveness, the standard LTDx sits in the middle of the LTDx driver family, and features the perfect balance of front and back weighting, making it playable for all golfers that want the ultimate combination of low spin and stability. Stock shafts include Mitsubishi's low-launching, low-spinning TENSEI AV RAW White, Project X's mid-launching, low-spinning HZRDUS RDX Blue, Project X's mid-launching, mid-spinning HZRDUS Smoke iM10, and UST's high-launching, high-spinning Helium NanoCore.
